thread.title: Deutsche Bank to Leave Wall Street for Midtown Manhattan

author: Keiko Morris
title: Deutsche Bank to Leave Wall Street for Midtown Manhattan

organizations.name: deutsche bank to leave wall street for midtown manhattan deutsche bank ag

text:
Deutsche Bank AG will move its North American headquarters from Wall Street to New York’s Columbus Circle adding yet another big name in the banking and securities industry to relocate to Midtown from the city’s traditional financial district.
After a 16-month search, the bank decided to move from its current location at 60 Wall St. to the Time Warner Center at Columbus Circle. The plan was announced to bank employees Friday afternoon in a memo from Tom Patrick, who became bank’s Americas chief executive last year.
